==Description== <!--T:10-->

<!--T:2-->
The '''Mesh FlipNormals''' command reverses, flips, the normals of mesh objects.

==Usage== <!--T:11-->

<!--T:3-->
# Select one or more mesh objects.
# There are several ways to invoke the command:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:Mesh_FlipNormals.svg|16px]] [[Mesh_FlipNormals|Flip normals]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|Meshes → [[Image:Mesh_FlipNormals.svg|16px]] Flip normals}} option from the menu.

==Notes== <!--T:12-->

<!--T:5-->
* For a clear indication of the orientation of the faces of mesh objects make sure the {{PropertyView|Lighting}} property of the mesh objects is set to {{Value|One side}}. The color of the back side of their faces will then depend on the backlight settings: {{MenuCommand|Edit → Preferences... → Display → Light Sources → Backlight: Intensity}}. See: [[Preferences_Editor#Light_Sources|Preferences Editor]].


